The paper deals with graph theory and algorithms for enumerating subgraphs based on topological minors. This falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DS). The use of decision diagrams also suggests a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the problem, which is related to computational complexity theory (cs.CC). Finally, the specific types of subgraphs considered (planar, outerplanar, series-parallel, and cactus) suggest a connection to graph theory (cs.DS) and possibly also game theory (cs.GT) in the case of cactus graphs.
